AMADIS Massinha was a version of the AMADIS Virtual Learning Environment developed for young children (6-10 y.o.). It features an user interface designed for children using colorful clay models.

This software was heavily used by children of  Porto Alegre Public School System, in Brazil, during the project ECSIC in 2003.

It was developed using a rudimentary in-house relative-object wrapper (the Model of MVC) called rddevel. Both code are included in order to make possible to run the software.


=Requirements=

This software requires PHP 4.2 in order to run. It is know that it doesn't run in newer versions.